    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel your <strong>potato[es]</strong> and chop into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pollock-smokie-and-toasted-ciabatta/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pollock-smokie-and-toasted-ciabatta/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pollock-smokie-and-toasted-ciabatta/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Melt 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>butter</strong> in a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms \u2013 this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and your <strong>clotted cream</strong> into the roux, a little at a time, and cook for 3-5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains \u2013 this is your <strong>b\u00e9chamel sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pollock-smokie-and-toasted-ciabatta/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>diced pollock </strong>dry with kitchen paper and chop into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Once the potatoes are tender, add the <strong>chopped diced pollock</strong>, <strong>cooked potatoes</strong> and <strong>chopped tomato</strong> to the b\u00e9chamel sauce</p><p>Add a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>pollock filling</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pollock-smokie-and-toasted-ciabatta/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>pollock filling </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> (use individual ones for fancy presentation!) and top with the <strong>grated cheese </strong>and a grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the dish[es] in the oven and cook for 12-15 min or until bubbling and golden and the fish is cooked through \u2013 this is your<strong> pollock smokie</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pollock-smokie-and-toasted-ciabatta/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pollock smokie is nearly ready, slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half and place in the <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until toasted</p><p>Once the pollock smokie is ready, remove the dish[es] from the oven and top with your <strong>smoked sea salt flakes</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pollock-smokie-and-toasted-ciabatta/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pollock smokie </strong>with the <strong>toasted ciabatta</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
